&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Pancreatico-biliary Cancer Surgery Nurse Specialist&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an experienced pancreatico-biliary nurse who is looking for a chance to develop their skills. We are looking for someone who has a particular interest in managing patients with bile duct/duodenal and pancreatic cancer, supporting them and their family pre/peri and post-surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the guidelines for clinical nurse specialist posts, the successful candidate with have obtained a nursing Degree or equivalent, or be willing to work towards this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Welsh Regional Centre for complex bile duct/duodenal and pancreatic surgery, you will be working alongside the band 7 CNS and caring for patients from across South East &amp; West Wales. There are 3 Consultant Surgeons along with a team of allied professionals. Working as part of a true Multidisciplinary team the successful candidate with have the opportunity to extend their knowledge and contribute to the team ethic and excellent patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will support patients and their families who are having complex surgery as well as those receiving a cancer diagnosis where surgery is not an option.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires excellent Communication skills and the ability to work autonomously on occasions. The successful candidate should be passionate about caring for patients with this particular diagnosis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
